
 pwd --> to display present working directory

mkdir --> to create or make directory

ls --> to list the files and folders

ls -lart --> to list all the files and folders with complete details

cd --> change directory(to login to particular directory)
cd .. --> to come back to previous folder(one step back)
cd - --> to go to previos directory
cd ~  --> to go to home directory

vi ---> to create and edit a file
  to insert code or data press i
  to save file --> esc and shift:wq!
  to come out of the file without saving --> esc and shift :q

cat --> to view the content of e
